main event: Two unidentified objects were sighted in the sky over the Canal Zone on 11 November 1952. The objects were observed to hover, maneuver, and disappear. The duration of the sighting was approximately 25 minutes.
interesting points: The objects appeared to be metallic, reflecting the sun's rays, and were moving at high speed.
The objects were observed to hover, maneuver, and disappear over the course of 25 minutes.
The sighting took place at 1500 hours on 11 November 1952.
The transcript of the log from the Air Force's Central Control Center details the movement and behavior of the objects during the sighting.
The conclusion was that the objects could not be identified as any known aircraft, and the sighting is classified as UNIDENTIFIED.
witnesses: Security Inspector at Atomic Energy Plant
